Author: Lorenzo Stoakes (Oracle) <ljs@kernel.org>

mm/huge_memory: deduplicate zap_huge_pmd() further by tracking state

This commit deduplicates folio_remove_rmap_pmd() and folio reference
handling in zap_huge_pmd() by tracking when a pmd entry removal requires
an rmap removal via a new needs_remove_rmap boolean.

> diff --git a/mm/huge_memory.c b/mm/huge_memory.c
> index bcc74b0172fa..f6caa6d35659 100644
> --- a/mm/huge_memory.c
> +++ b/mm/huge_memory.c

[ ... ]

> @@ -2459,17 +2461,15 @@ bool zap_huge_pmd(struct mmu_gather *tlb, struct vm_area_struct *vma,
>  		goto out;
>  	}
>  
> -	if (pmd_present(orig_pmd)) {
> +	is_present = pmd_present(orig_pmd);
> +	if (is_present) {
>  		folio = pmd_folio(orig_pmd);
> -
> -		flush_needed = true;
> -		folio_remove_rmap_pmd(folio, &folio->page, vma);
> -		WARN_ON_ONCE(folio_mapcount(folio) < 0);
> +		needs_remove_rmap = true;
>  	} else if (pmd_is_valid_softleaf(orig_pmd)) {
>  		const softleaf_t entry = softleaf_from_pmd(orig_pmd);
>  
>  		folio = softleaf_to_folio(entry);
> -
> +		needs_remove_rmap = folio_is_device_private(folio);

Does this code correctly distinguish between device-private swap entries
and migration entries for device-private folios?

Since pmd_is_valid_softleaf() matches both device-private and migration swap
entries, if this is a migration entry for a device-private folio,
softleaf_to_folio() will return the source device-private folio, making
folio_is_device_private() true.

Because migration entries do not hold a pmd rmap or a folio reference
themselves (those are dropped when the migration entry is created), would
setting needs_remove_rmap to true here cause a mapcount underflow and
use-after-free when folio_remove_rmap_pmd() and folio_put() are called
later in this function?

Should this check the entry type directly instead, such as using
softleaf_is_device_private(entry)?

>  		if (!thp_migration_supported())
>  			WARN_ONCE(1, "Non present huge pmd without pmd migration enabled!");
>  	} else {

